Class HashTable_LP<Key,Value>

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:

public class HashTable_LP<Key,Value> extends Object
Class which implements ST (symbol table) by using Linear Probing (Open Addressing).

  • Field Details

    • m

      protected final int m
      The size of the array in this hash table. This determines the capacity of the hash table and plays a key role in distributing the keys across the buckets to minimize collisions. The value of m is constant and initialized at the time of constructing the HashTable instance.

  • Constructor Details

    • HashTable_LP

      public HashTable_LP(int capacity)
      Constructs a HashTable_LP instance with the specified initial capacity. This constructor initializes necessary data structures and calculates the required properties for internal storage.
      Parameters:
      capacity - the initial capacity of the hash table. It determines the number of slots in the underlying storage, rounded to the nearest power of two.
